?planes could be distinctly heard as they passed overhead : heavy anti-aircraft gun fire going on : good moon though misty air
Sunday Sept 30th
Dartford Hosp : transferred to ward A.15 : Holy Comm at 10 am in the Chapel very nice ; church at 10.45 am also nice : band for orchestra fair few nurses W.L. [Women's Legion] girls there : another air raid at night
Monday Oct 1st
Dartford Hosp : inspected bt Dr in morn : wound nearly healed but thigh still stiff : said he would leave the two pieces of shell in so long as they didn't interfere with my movements : sent a Hun book a few clippings to Mum : Wilkie self strolled to Dartford : fair sized place : rested in Y.M.C.A. then